title: MAFS star Jessika Power 'WILL enter Love Island as an intruder'
text:
For weeks, Married At First Sight's Jessika Power has been dropping hints that she will appear on Love Island Australia as an 'intruder'.

And she could be jetting to Fiji sooner rather than later, with NW reporting she has been 'put on stand-by' by Channel Nine executives.

According to the magazine, Love Island producers hope she will 'stir up drama' and boost ratings for the raunchy reality show.

Coming soon? MAFS star Jessika Power could be appearing on Love Island Australia sooner rather than later, with NW reporting she has been 'put on stand-by' by Channel Nine producers

Jessika, 27, told the publication that she is looking forward to confronting Vanessa Sierra on Love Island, after the pair feuded on social media.

'I'm itching to get in so I can confront Vanessa and expose her for who she truly is,' she said.

A Channel Nine spokesperson said there is no truth to NW's report and Jessika will not be appearing on Love Island.

Vanessa, 25, is the ex-girlfriend of Jessika's older brother Rhyce Power.

Such a tease! For weeks, Jessika has been dropping hints that she will appear on Love Island Australia as an 'intruder'

Here comes trouble! According to NW magazine, Love Island producers hope Jessika will 'stir up drama' and boost ratings for the raunchy reality show

The model and former topless waitress publicly accused Rhyce of assaulting her on a fitness holiday in Thailand earlier this year, which he denies.

In a recent interview with The Kyle and Jackie O Show, Jessika said she was keen to gatecrash the series so she could confront Vanessa directly.

Referring to her rival, she said: 'When the [Love Island] promo came out I was just like, "Oh, that's why the social climbing is happening".'

Women at war! Jessika, 27, said she is looking forward to confronting Vanessa Sierra (pictured) on Love Island, after the pair feuded on social media

Exes: Vanessa is the ex-girlfriend of Jessika's brother Rhyce Power (left). She publicly accused Rhyce of assaulting her on a fitness holiday in Thailand earlier this year, which he denies

She also revealed that Vanessa had been 'slagging [her] off' on social media with disparaging comments.

It comes after Jessika 'hooked up' with a female friend named Cherie during a boozy girls' weekend in Cairns earlier this month.

They made no effort to hide their frisky behaviour while celebrating Mad Monday, with an onlooker saying 'they wanted people to notice them'.
description: For weeks, Married At First Sight's Jessika Power has been dropping hints that she will appear on Love Island Australia as an 'intruder'.
authors: Jo Scrimshire For Daily Mail Australia
